# =============================================================================
# OPTIONAL REVIEWERS (Not required but recommended)
# =============================================================================
# These reviewers will be notified but won't block merges
# Uncomment to enable optional reviews
# ^/src/experimental/          @innovation-team #optional
# /proof-of-concept/           @architecture-committee #optional

# =============================================================================
# NOTES
# =============================================================================
# 1. Team handles should be GitHub team names (e.g., @backend-team)
# 2. Individual users can be specified (e.g., @username)
# 3. Multiple owners can be specified per pattern (space-separated)
# 4. Patterns follow gitignore-style matching
# 5. More specific patterns override general ones
# 6. Use #optional suffix for non-blocking reviews
# 
# Review Requirements by Risk Level:
# - Low Risk (docs, tests): 1 approval from any owner
# - Medium Risk (bug fixes, features): 1-2 approvals including code owner
# - High Risk (architecture, core logic): 2+ approvals including domain expert
# - Critical Risk (security, infra): 2+ approvals including security/sre team

# =============================================================================
# MAINTENANCE
# =============================================================================
# This file should be reviewed quarterly by:
# - Engineering Leadership
# - Platform Team
# - Security Team
# 
# Update team assignments when:
# - Team structure changes
# - New domains are added
# - Ownership responsibilities shift
